---
// Guidance — brownfield onboarding hero.
// Sibling to SecondaryFlows.astro: same 3-block grammar, different gesture.
// Blueprint folds (vertical compression). Guidance mirrors (lateral projection,
// per-depth). The two hero figures sit adjacent on the page and intentionally
// encode orthogonal motions so the eye reads them as a pair, not a repeat.
---

<section id="guidance">
	<div class="container">
		<p class="kicker">§ guidance · per-folder shadow docs</p>
		<h2>Context that narrows as the agent descends.</h2>
		<p class="gd__lede">
			Inline <code>CLAUDE.md</code> works on greenfield, but it doesn't scale to a
			codebase nobody can fit in their head.
			<strong><code>/skill:annotate-guidance</code> writes a parallel <code>.rpiv/guidance/</code> tree of compact <code>architecture.md</code> files</strong>,
			one per folder you care about, resolved per-depth and injected at
			<code>session_start</code> and on every <code>tool_call</code>, so context
			narrows as the agent navigates deeper.
		</p>

		<figure class="gd-flow" aria-label="Annotate-guidance reads the existing codebase, writes a parallel shadow tree, and the Pi agent reads it per-depth at session_start and tool_call.">
			{/* ── BLOCK 01 — input (existing brownfield codebase) ── */}
			<article class="gd-block gd-block--input">
				<header class="gd-block__head">
					<p class="gd-kicker mono">01 · input</p>
					<h3 class="mono gd-name">existing repo</h3>
				</header>
				<p class="gd-desc">
					Two parallel passes map the tree, name the architecture, and pull
					idiomatic patterns out of each layer.
				</p>

				{/* mini story-SVG: a brownfield staircase tree, sage strokes,
				    one ochre CLAUDE.md leaf calling out the legacy fallback. */}
				<svg class="gd-mini" viewBox="0 0 200 110" width="200" height="110" aria-hidden="true" preserveAspectRatio="xMidYMid meet">
					<g fill="none" stroke="var(--sage-deep)" stroke-linecap="round">
						{/* trunk */}
						<path d="M14,16 L14,98" stroke-width="0.7" opacity="0.55" />
						{/* depth-1 branches */}
						<path d="M14,30 L28,30" stroke-width="0.7" opacity="0.55" />
						<path d="M14,52 L28,52" stroke-width="0.7" opacity="0.55" />
						<path d="M14,78 L28,78" stroke-width="0.7" opacity="0.55" />
					</g>
					{/* folder + file rows */}
					<g font-family="var(--font-mono)" font-size="9" fill="var(--text-quiet)" letter-spacing="0.02em">
						<text x="32" y="20">packages/</text>
						<text x="44" y="34">pi/</text>
						<text x="44" y="56">site/</text>
						<text x="44" y="82">tools/</text>
					</g>
					{/* file ticks beside each folder */}
					<g stroke="var(--washi-soft)" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-width="0.6" opacity="0.55">
						<line x1="100" y1="34" x2="138" y2="34" />
						<line x1="100" y1="56" x2="146" y2="56" />
						<line x1="100" y1="82" x2="132" y2="82" />
						<line x1="100" y1="92" x2="142" y2="92" />
					</g>
					{/* legacy CLAUDE.md leaf — ochre, the cascade respects it */}
					<g>
						<rect x="150" y="10" width="44" height="14" rx="1.5"
							fill="var(--ink)" stroke="var(--ochre)" stroke-width="0.8" opacity="0.85" />
						<text x="172" y="20" text-anchor="middle"
							font-family="var(--font-mono)" font-size="7" fill="var(--ochre)"
							letter-spacing="0.06em">CLAUDE.md</text>
					</g>
					<g fill="none" stroke="var(--ochre)" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-width="0.5" opacity="0.45" stroke-dasharray="2 2">
						<path d="M138,18 L150,17" />
					</g>
					<text x="14" y="108" font-family="var(--font-mono)" font-size="7" fill="var(--text-distant)" letter-spacing="0.18em">BROWNFIELD</text>
				</svg>

				<p class="gd-meta mono">
					<span class="gd-meta__arrow">→</span>
					<span class="gd-meta__ref">scans current repo · respects <code>.gitignore</code></span>
				</p>
			</article>

			{/* ── CONNECTOR 01 → 02 — calligraphy brushstroke labelled READS ── */}
			<div class="gd-link" aria-hidden="true">
				<svg class="gd-link__brush" viewBox="0 0 120 80" width="120" height="80" preserveAspectRatio="xMidYMid meet">
					<g fill="none" stroke-linecap="round">
						<path d="M8,32 Q42,26 100,30" stroke="var(--ochre)" stroke-width="0.5" opacity="0.32" />
						<path d="M6,40 Q40,36 102,40" stroke="var(--washi-soft)" stroke-width="1.6" opacity="0.85" />
						<path d="M8,48 Q42,44 100,46" stroke="var(--sage)" stroke-width="0.5" opacity="0.22" />
						<path d="M96,32 L112,40 L96,48" stroke="var(--washi-soft)" stroke-width="1.4" opacity="0.85" />
						<path d="M97,34 L109,40 L97,46" stroke="var(--ochre)" stroke-width="0.5" opacity="0.32" />
					</g>
					<text x="60" y="68" text-anchor="middle"
						font-family="var(--font-mono)" font-size="9"
						fill="var(--text-distant)" letter-spacing="0.18em">READS</text>
				</svg>
			</div>

			{/* ── BLOCK 02 — HERO annotate-guidance with MIRROR diagram ── */}
			<article class="gd-block gd-block--hero">
				<div class="gd-hero__wash" aria-hidden="true"></div>

				<header class="gd-block__head">
					<p class="gd-kicker mono gd-kicker--hero">02 · shadow tree</p>
					<h3 class="mono gd-name gd-name--hero">/skill:annotate-guidance</h3>
				</header>

				{/* THE MIRROR DIAGRAM — lateral projection.
				    The motion of this figure is LEFT-TO-RIGHT, four times in parallel.
				    Source tree on the left, .rpiv/guidance/ shadow tree on the right,
				    a vertical seam between them. Four ochre arcs project each source
				    folder onto its mirror architecture.md across the seam — one per
				    depth. Counterpoint to Blueprint's single top-down fold. */}
				<svg class="gd-mirror" viewBox="0 0 360 218" width="360" height="218" aria-label="Source tree on the left mirrors into a shadow guidance tree on the right; one architecture.md per depth, injected at session_start and tool_call." preserveAspectRatio="xMidYMid meet">

					{/* — HEADER BAND — three column captions on a thin baseline — */}
					<text x="14" y="12" font-family="var(--font-mono)" font-size="7"
						fill="var(--text-distant)" letter-spacing="0.18em">SOURCE</text>
					<text x="180" y="12" text-anchor="middle"
						font-family="var(--font-mono)" font-size="7"
						fill="var(--text-distant)" letter-spacing="0.18em">.rpiv/</text>
					<text x="346" y="12" text-anchor="end"
						font-family="var(--font-mono)" font-size="7"
						fill="var(--text-distant)" letter-spacing="0.18em">SHADOW</text>

					{/* — SEAM — the .rpiv/ boundary, a quiet vertical hairline — */}
					<line x1="180" y1="22" x2="180" y2="170"
						stroke="var(--rule-strong)" stroke-width="0.6"
						stroke-dasharray="1 4" opacity="0.65" />

					{/* — SOURCE TREE — folder glyphs as actual folder shapes
					    (tab + body), name labels only — no underline ticks. */}
					{[
						{ y: 52,  indent: 16, name: "packages/" },
						{ y: 88,  indent: 28, name: "pi/" },
						{ y: 124, indent: 40, name: "skills/" },
						{ y: 160, indent: 52, name: "annotate-…/" },
					].map((row) => (
						<g>
							{/* folder shape: small tab on top-left of body */}
							<path
								d={`M${row.indent},${row.y - 1} L${row.indent + 5},${row.y - 1} L${row.indent + 7},${row.y - 3} L${row.indent + 14},${row.y - 3} L${row.indent + 14},${row.y + 6} L${row.indent},${row.y + 6} Z`}
								fill="none" stroke="var(--sage-deep)"
								stroke-width="0.7" opacity="0.7"
								stroke-linejoin="round" />
							<text x={row.indent + 18} y={row.y + 3}
								font-family="var(--font-mono)" font-size="8.5"
								fill="var(--text-quiet)" letter-spacing="0.02em">{row.name}</text>
						</g>
					))}

					{/* — SHADOW TREE — portrait page glyphs (20×22) with a folded
					    corner. Slimmer than before so the doc reads compact and
					    the architecture.md label sits closer to the gesture's
					    landing point. */}
					{[
						{ y: 52,  indent: 200 },
						{ y: 88,  indent: 212 },
						{ y: 124, indent: 224 },
						{ y: 160, indent: 236 },
					].map((row) => (
						<g>
							{/* page outline: 14-wide body + 6-wide corner notch = 20 total,
							    22 tall (y-11 to y+11). */}
							<path
								d={`M${row.indent},${row.y - 11} L${row.indent + 14},${row.y - 11} L${row.indent + 20},${row.y - 5} L${row.indent + 20},${row.y + 11} L${row.indent},${row.y + 11} Z`}
								fill="var(--ink)" stroke="var(--washi-soft)"
								stroke-width="0.7" opacity="0.92"
								stroke-linejoin="round" />
							{/* folded-corner bracket — vertical drop + horizontal lip */}
							<path
								d={`M${row.indent + 14},${row.y - 11} L${row.indent + 14},${row.y - 5} L${row.indent + 20},${row.y - 5}`}
								fill="none" stroke="var(--washi-soft)"
								stroke-width="0.5" opacity="0.55"
								stroke-linejoin="round" />
							{/* internal text-lines: title (shorter, brighter) + two body lines.
							    Constrained to the 14px body width so they don't poke into
							    the corner notch. */}
							<line x1={row.indent + 3} y1={row.y - 3} x2={row.indent + 9} y2={row.y - 3}
								stroke="var(--washi-soft)" stroke-width="0.6" opacity="0.65" />
							<line x1={row.indent + 3} y1={row.y + 2} x2={row.indent + 12} y2={row.y + 2}
								stroke="var(--washi-soft)" stroke-width="0.5" opacity="0.45" />
							<line x1={row.indent + 3} y1={row.y + 7} x2={row.indent + 11} y2={row.y + 7}
								stroke="var(--washi-soft)" stroke-width="0.5" opacity="0.45" />
							{/* label — 6px gap from doc edge, font matches source folder names */}
							<text x={row.indent + 26} y={row.y + 3}
								font-family="var(--font-mono)" font-size="8.5"
								fill="var(--washi-soft)" letter-spacing="0.02em">architecture.md</text>
						</g>
					))}

					{/* — MIRROR ARCS — triple-stroke calligraphy with hand-drawn
					    chevron at the right endpoint (no SVG marker — keep the
					    ink-brush feel consistent with bp-link__brush). */}
					{[
						{ y: 52,  lx: 88,  rx: 198 },
						{ y: 88,  lx: 70,  rx: 210 },
						{ y: 124, lx: 100, rx: 222 },
						{ y: 160, lx: 132, rx: 234 },
					].map((arc) => {
						const mid = (arc.lx + arc.rx) / 2;
						return (
							<g fill="none" stroke-linecap="round">
								{/* faint ochre echo above */}
								<path d={`M${arc.lx},${arc.y - 3} Q${mid},${arc.y - 14} ${arc.rx - 2},${arc.y - 3}`}
									stroke="var(--ochre)" stroke-width="0.5" opacity="0.32" />
								{/* dominant washi-soft brushstroke */}
								<path d={`M${arc.lx},${arc.y} Q${mid},${arc.y - 11} ${arc.rx - 2},${arc.y}`}
									stroke="var(--washi-soft)" stroke-width="1.3" opacity="0.85" />
								{/* faint sage echo below */}
								<path d={`M${arc.lx},${arc.y + 3} Q${mid},${arc.y - 8} ${arc.rx - 2},${arc.y + 3}`}
									stroke="var(--sage)" stroke-width="0.5" opacity="0.22" />
								{/* hand-drawn chevron arrowhead — two stacked strokes */}
								<path d={`M${arc.rx - 6},${arc.y - 3} L${arc.rx - 1},${arc.y} L${arc.rx - 6},${arc.y + 3}`}
									stroke="var(--washi-soft)" stroke-width="1.2" opacity="0.85" />
								<path d={`M${arc.rx - 5},${arc.y - 2} L${arc.rx - 2},${arc.y} L${arc.rx - 5},${arc.y + 2}`}
									stroke="var(--ochre)" stroke-width="0.5" opacity="0.4" />
							</g>
						);
					})}

					{/* — DEPTH LADDER — tick on seam + tabular digit BELOW the
					    row, shifted left of seam so it leans toward the
					    source-side gesture instead of floating dead-center. */}
					{[
						{ y: 52,  d: 0 },
						{ y: 88,  d: 1 },
						{ y: 124, d: 2 },
						{ y: 160, d: 3 },
					].map((row) => (
						<g>
							<line x1="177" y1={row.y} x2="183" y2={row.y}
								stroke="var(--ochre)" stroke-width="0.8" opacity="0.75" />
							<text x="168" y={row.y + 16} text-anchor="middle"
								font-family="var(--font-mono)" font-size="6.5"
								fill="var(--ochre)" opacity="0.8"
								letter-spacing="0.06em">d={row.d}</text>
						</g>
					))}

					{/* — INJECTION POINTS BAND — runtime strip, distinct from the
					    tree-mirror gesture above. Two chip glyphs in matching
					    style: same rect+text grammar, different stroke colors
					    to distinguish lifecycle (sage) from runtime (ochre). */}
					<line x1="0" y1="184" x2="360" y2="184"
						stroke="var(--rule-strong)" stroke-width="0.5" opacity="0.55" />
					<text x="14" y="200"
						font-family="var(--font-mono)" font-size="7"
						fill="var(--text-distant)" letter-spacing="0.18em">INJECTION POINTS</text>

					{/* session_start chip (left of seam) — sage outline,
					    signifying lifecycle event */}
					<g>
						<rect x="132" y="192" width="86" height="14" rx="2"
							fill="var(--ink-raised)" stroke="var(--sage)"
							stroke-width="0.7" opacity="0.85" />
						<text x="175" y="202" text-anchor="middle"
							font-family="var(--font-mono)" font-size="8"
							fill="var(--washi-soft)" letter-spacing="0.04em">session_start</text>
					</g>

					{/* small dotted connector between chips — implies "and" */}
					<g fill="none" stroke="var(--washi-soft)" stroke-linecap="round" opacity="0.45">
						<path d="M222,199 L236,199" stroke-width="0.6" stroke-dasharray="2 2" />
					</g>

					{/* tool_call chip (right of seam) — ochre outline,
					    signifying recurring runtime call */}
					<g>
						<rect x="240" y="192" width="68" height="14" rx="2"
							fill="var(--ink-raised)" stroke="var(--ochre)"
							stroke-width="0.7" opacity="0.95" />
						<text x="274" y="202" text-anchor="middle"
							font-family="var(--font-mono)" font-size="8"
							fill="var(--washi-soft)" letter-spacing="0.04em">tool_call</text>
					</g>

					{/* trailing dotted rail — implies "every tool_call, ongoing" */}
					<g fill="none" stroke="var(--washi-soft)" stroke-linecap="round" opacity="0.3">
						<path d="M312,199 L344,199" stroke-width="0.5" stroke-dasharray="2 3" />
					</g>
				</svg>

				<p class="gd-desc gd-desc--hero">
					A shadow tree mirrors the source. Each folder's <code>architecture.md</code>
					is the smallest thing the agent needs to act correctly <em>here</em>,
					not the whole repo.
				</p>

				{/* Trade ledger — gain / cost two-column comparison.
				    Sage label = gains; ochre label = cost. Same idiom as Blueprint. */}
				<div class="gd-trade">
					<div class="gd-trade__col gd-trade__col--gain">
						<p class="mono gd-trade__label">gain</p>
						<ul class="gd-trade__list">
							<li>context follows the agent into deep folders</li>
							<li>zero source-code noise: docs live alongside, not inside</li>
						</ul>
					</div>
					<div class="gd-trade__col gd-trade__col--cost">
						<p class="mono gd-trade__label">cost</p>
						<ul class="gd-trade__list">
							<li>shadow tree drifts after structural changes: regenerate</li>
						</ul>
					</div>
				</div>

				{/* Meta keeps the path only — the injection points are visualised
				   in the SVG band and named in the lede, so restating them
				   here just produced a redundant wrapped second line. */}
				<p class="gd-meta mono">
					<span class="gd-meta__arrow">→</span>
					<code>.rpiv/guidance/&lt;sub&gt;/architecture.md</code>
				</p>

				{/* corner sumi-ink ornament — mirrored vs Blueprint's bottom-right
				    so two adjacent hero figures don't share the same corner. */}
				<svg class="gd-hero__ornament" viewBox="0 0 160 110" width="160" height="110" aria-hidden="true">
					<g fill="none" stroke="var(--ochre)" stroke-linecap="round" opacity="0.45">
						<path d="M150,98 q-26,-58 -78,-78 q-40,-15 -66,32" stroke-width="1.1" />
						<path d="M138,104 q-22,-44 -64,-58 q-34,-11 -60,18" stroke-width="0.6" opacity="0.55" />
						<path d="M126,108 q-18,-30 -50,-44" stroke-width="0.4" opacity="0.4" />
						<circle cx="14" cy="44" r="2" />
						<circle cx="120" cy="84" r="1.4" opacity="0.7" />
						<circle cx="60" cy="22" r="1.2" opacity="0.6" />
					</g>
				</svg>
			</article>

			{/* ── CONNECTOR 02 → 03 — calligraphy brushstroke labelled INJECTS ── */}
			<div class="gd-link" aria-hidden="true">
				<svg class="gd-link__brush" viewBox="0 0 120 80" width="120" height="80" preserveAspectRatio="xMidYMid meet">
					<g fill="none" stroke-linecap="round">
						<path d="M8,32 Q42,26 100,30" stroke="var(--ochre)" stroke-width="0.5" opacity="0.32" />
						<path d="M6,40 Q40,36 102,40" stroke="var(--washi-soft)" stroke-width="1.6" opacity="0.85" />
						<path d="M8,48 Q42,44 100,46" stroke="var(--sage)" stroke-width="0.5" opacity="0.22" />
						<path d="M96,32 L112,40 L96,48" stroke="var(--washi-soft)" stroke-width="1.4" opacity="0.85" />
						<path d="M97,34 L109,40 L97,46" stroke="var(--ochre)" stroke-width="0.5" opacity="0.32" />
					</g>
					<text x="60" y="68" text-anchor="middle"
						font-family="var(--font-mono)" font-size="9"
						fill="var(--text-distant)" letter-spacing="0.18em">INJECTS</text>
				</svg>
			</div>

			{/* ── BLOCK 03 — output (pi agent · per-depth context) ── */}
			<article class="gd-block gd-block--output">
				<header class="gd-block__head">
					<p class="gd-kicker mono">03 · output</p>
					<h3 class="mono gd-name">pi · per-depth context</h3>
				</header>
				<p class="gd-desc">
					On <code>session_start</code>, root guidance loads. On every
					<code>read</code>/<code>edit</code>/<code>write</code>, the closest
					ancestor <code>architecture.md</code> for the touched path injects too,
					silently, as a hidden context message.
				</p>

				{/* mini story-SVG: 3 tool calls, each branching to its ancestor arch.md */}
				<svg class="gd-mini" viewBox="0 0 200 110" width="200" height="110" aria-hidden="true" preserveAspectRatio="xMidYMid meet">
					{/* call rail */}
					<g fill="none" stroke="var(--sage-deep)" stroke-linecap="round">
						<path d="M14,18 L14,94" stroke-width="0.7" opacity="0.55" />
					</g>
					{/* 3 tool-call chips */}
					{[
						{ y: 24,  name: "read",  op: 0.95 },
						{ y: 56,  name: "edit",  op: 0.75 },
						{ y: 88,  name: "write", op: 0.55 },
					].map((c) => (
						<g>
							<rect x="20" y={c.y - 7} width="44" height="14" rx="1.5"
								fill="var(--ink-raised)" stroke="var(--sage-deep)"
								stroke-width="0.7" opacity={c.op} />
							<text x="42" y={c.y + 3} text-anchor="middle"
								font-family="var(--font-mono)" font-size="8"
								fill="var(--text-quiet)" letter-spacing="0.02em">{c.name}</text>
							{/* injection branch out to ancestor doc */}
							<g fill="none" stroke="var(--ochre)" stroke-linecap="round"
								stroke-width="0.7" opacity={0.35 + c.op * 0.4}>
								<path d={`M64,${c.y} L120,${c.y}`} stroke-dasharray="3 2" />
								<path d={`M116,${c.y - 3} L120,${c.y} L116,${c.y + 3}`} />
							</g>
							{/* tiny doc glyph at the tip */}
							<g>
								<rect x="124" y={c.y - 6} width="22" height="12" rx="1"
									fill="var(--ink)" stroke="var(--washi-soft)"
									stroke-width="0.5" opacity={0.55 + c.op * 0.3} />
								<text x="135" y={c.y + 2} text-anchor="middle"
									font-family="var(--font-mono)" font-size="6.5"
									fill="var(--ochre)" letter-spacing="0.06em">▲ARCH</text>
							</g>
							<text x="152" y={c.y + 2}
								font-family="var(--font-mono)" font-size="7"
								fill="var(--text-distant)" letter-spacing="0.04em" opacity="0.85">d={3 - Math.floor((c.y - 24) / 32)}</text>
						</g>
					))}
					<text x="14" y="108"
						font-family="var(--font-mono)" font-size="7"
						fill="var(--text-distant)" letter-spacing="0.18em">PER-DEPTH</text>
				</svg>

				<p class="gd-meta mono">
					<span class="gd-meta__arrow">→</span>
					<span class="gd-meta__ref">pi · agent runtime</span>
				</p>
			</article>
		</figure>

		{/* see-also: migrate-to-guidance is the natural neighbour.
		   No own border — the figure's border-bottom is the divider. */}
		<p class="gd__seealso mono">
			<span class="gd__seealso-label">see also</span>
			<span class="chip">/skill:migrate-to-guidance</span>
			<span class="gd__seealso-text">convert an existing <code>CLAUDE.md</code> project into the guidance system.</span>
		</p>
	</div>
</section>

<style>
	#guidance h2 { margin-bottom: var(--space-5); }

	.gd__lede {
		color: var(--text-quiet);
		margin-bottom: var(--space-7);
		max-width: 64ch;
	}
	.gd__lede strong {
		color: var(--washi);
